# Some commands , tips and tricks , and interesting notes.

# Linux related

## to get the ip4 address(es)
$ ip -o -4 a

##  list all listening ports along with the process name and the user running it:
$ sudo lsof -i -P -n | grep LISTEN | awk '{printf "%-10s %-10s %-20s\n", $1, $3, $9}'

# Docker related

$ docker run -d --rm -p 5000:5000 test:v1   --->  (--rm) is useful , as it deletes the exited containers automatically 

## to get network info from a running container
$ docker inspect <container_name_or_id> | grep -E -i "Network|IPAddress|Gateway"

